              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3INDTAT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "C,2007TOKYO,2,425,2007",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "C,2007TOKYO,2,425,2007",
                    "doi": null,
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "C",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "2007TOKYO",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "2",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "425"
                      },
                      "date": 2007
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "It wasn't published as Nucl.Phys. A805 (2008) 425-427"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "3INDTRM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "BARC-TIFR pelletron accelerator",
                " (VDGT)IOP-Bhubanuswar pelletron facility"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "thin target of Si-28 (thickness 192 microgram/cm2)",
                "sandwiched between 40 microgram/cm2 of Au(in front)",
                "and 100 microgram/cm2 of Au (back) was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The gamma rays emmitted from the evaporation",
                "residues were detected using Compton suppressed",
                "Clover/HPGe detector placed at 55 deg with respect to",
                "beam direction."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SOLST",
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " measurement of angular",
                "distribution of evaporation of alpha particles was",
                "done using two telescopes (25 mu-m, 300mu-m) and two",
                "monitors were placed at forward angles(+-9.8 deg) for",
                "beam normalisation purpose."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "gamma ray method and alpha evaporation technique"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The important residues from the fusion of 7-Li+ 28-Si",
                "were diagonised by the characteristic gamma ray spectra",
                "and these were 29-Si, 30-Si, 32-S, 33-S, 30-P and 33-P.",
                "The total gamma-ray cross section was obtained by",
                "summing all the cross sections of gamma rays 2.208 MeV,",
                " (29-Si), 1.273+1.263 MeV(29-Si+30-Si), 2.235+2.230 MeV",
                " (30-Si+32-S), 1.967 MeV(33-S), 0.677 MeV(30-P), 1.847",
                "MeV(33-P). Evaporation alpha cross sections were",
                "extracted from the alpha spectra at different angles",
                "and these were analysed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "the total error in fusion cross section",
                "has been estimated to be about +-14%"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
